---
title: Cranberry-Drizzled Duck Breasts with Watercress Salad and Mashed Potatoes
description: Cranberry sauce is for more than just turkey. Here, we’re using it to make crispy, pan-seared duck breasts truly dazzle. The rich poultry is enlivened by its tart fruitiness, resulting in a wave of bold flavors that travel over the tongue and linger. Add some buttery mashed potatoes and a peppery watercress salad to the side, and you’ve got a meal that is sure to be a favorite in your kitchen through fall and beyond.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cranberry-drizzled-duck-breasts-f7ce5d1e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cranberry-drizzled-duck-breasts-d6d6ddac.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cranberry-drizzled-duck-breasts-59a83ce5043c3c74260709c3
author: HelloFresh
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: North America
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 950 kcal
  fat: 71 g
  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 450 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Mince @Garlic{2%clove}. Make shallow slits in @Duck Breasts{12%ounce} skin in a crosshatch pattern. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to a large pan skin-side down and place over medium heat. Cook until fat is rendered and skin is crisp, ~{10-15%minutes}. Flip and cook to desired doneness, ~{2-5%minutes} more.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with a large pinch of salt and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot{}.

While duck and potatoes cook, place garlic and @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{} and microwave on high until melted. Strip @Thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce} and @Lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have ¼ cup minced shallot.

Add garlic butter and @Milk{⅓%cup} to pot with potatoes. Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add more milk as needed to give potatoes a creamy consistency.

Cover to keep warm.

Once duck is finished cooking, remove from pan and set aside to rest. Pour off all but 1 TBSP duck fat from pan, then return pan to medium heat. Add shallot and thyme leaves. Cook until shallot is softened, ~{3%minutes}. Add @Chicken Demi-Glace{1}, @Cranberry Jam{1%ounce}, and ¼ cup water, stirring to break up jam. Let simmer until syrupy, about ~{2%minutes}. Stir in a squeeze of lemon. Season with pepper and more lemon (to taste).

Toss @Watercress{2%ounce} and tomatoes with a squeeze of lemon and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Thinly slice duck crosswise. Divide potatoes and duck between plates, then drizzle with sauce. Serve with salad on the side.